Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Laboratory results are generally within normal limits. There is a mildly low creatinine, likely reflecting reduced muscle mass in this elderly patient, and a slightly elevated chloride, which may be clinically insignificant if the patient is asymptomatic. Glucose control and lipid profile are good. No acute abnormalities detected. Recommend clinical correlation.
